Durban - The board of the RK Khan Hospital has denied claims someone from their nursing staff had informed a Chatsworth man his mother had died when she was still alive. A week ago, Desigan Padayachee claimed he received a call on a private number from a nurse who had informed him that his mother, Muthiyaluamma Padayachee, 75, who was a patient, had died. Read: Hoax death call angers family The chairman of the hospital board, Reverend Cyril Pillay, said the nurse in charge denied making the call. “The nursing staff deal with grieving relatives multiple times on a daily basis and are trained to deal with them with compassion and empathy. "The sister in charge of the ward that night is someone with over 25 years of experience and is known to be compassionate and caring.” - POST